{"title":"Pro bike: Tadej Pogačar’s World Championships-winning Colnago V4Rs","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-world-championships-colnago-v4rs-2024","date":1727712100000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-world-championships-colnago-v4rs-2024\">Pro bike: Tadej Pogačar’s World Championships-winning Colnago V4Rs</a></p>\n\n<p>Tadej Pogačar’s World Championships road race victory was completely expected, but amazing nonetheless. The Slovenian attacked from the peloton with 100km to go and never looked back.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>He held off the chasing groups riding this special edition Colnago V4Rs, with a paintjob to celebrate his achievements this year, including yellow for the Tour de France, pink for the Giro d’Italia and blue for the Giro’s <em>maglia azzurra </em>KOM jersey. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Techwise it’s very sponsor-faithful, despite his recent criticism of the accuracy of his power meter. Points of note are the funky AbsoluteBlack brake pads, Continental’s TT tyres – which are actually a popular choice in road races – and the funky blue derailleur hanger – which is almost certainly just there to be blue.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frameset: </strong>Colnago V4Rs</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Groupset:</strong> Shimano Dura-Ace Di2</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Crankset: </strong>54/40T</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Power meter:</strong> Shimano Dura-Ace</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Pedals:</strong> Shimano Dura-Ace</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wheels:</strong> Enve SES 4.5</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tyres:</strong> Continental Grand Prix 5000 TT </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Handlebar/stem:</strong> Enve SES AR</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bar tape:</strong> Colnago</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Seatpost:</strong> Colnago V4Rs Carbon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Saddle:</strong> Prologo Nago R4 147</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bottle cages:</strong> Elite Leggero Carbon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Computer:</strong> Wahoo</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Extras: </strong>AbsoluteBlack Graphenpads brake pads, fun blue derailleur hanger</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-4.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Xavier Pereyron</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-6-647x970.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-6-647x970.jpg 647w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/pogacar-worlds-bike-2024-xp-6-200x300.jpg 200w, https://